event: response.output_text.done
data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_052bcabf6a4cf7320169e3dc14cc048194becd19bad1c1bee4","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":355,"text":"1) **Make a “bookmark + page holder”**\n- Unfold the paperclip fully.\n- Bend one end into a small hook shape.\n- Slide the hook over the edge of a page.\n- Use the rest of the clip to gently press the page flat (like a lightweight clamp).\n- Fold it back/adjust so it grips without tearing.\n\n2) **Create a quick cable/cord organizer**\n- Straighten the paperclip halfway so it forms a simple “U” or bracket.\n- Slide the paperclip around a portion of the cable (near where it bunches).\n- Twist one arm slightly so it pinches the cable in place.\n- Repeat with a second clip if needed to prevent sliding.\n- Wrap the cable neatly and use the clips to keep the sections aligned.\n\n3) **Build a simple “thumbtack for light items” (temporary poster/notes)**\n- Unfold the paperclip, then curl one end into a tight loop or hook.\n- Push the hook tip into a wall/board lightly (it’s best on softer surfaces like foam board or cork).\n- Bend the longer portion to act as a small stand/holder.\n- Slide the note or edge of the paper under the hook area to hang it.\n- Remove by pulling straight out and bending back carefully for reuse."}

